# Copy to your local agent/runtime environment and fill in values there.
# Never commit real credentials.

# Google Drive OAuth token file (authorized-user JSON) used by the research-wiki tools
# (research_scan.py, scan_triage_apply.py, pdf_backlog_triage.py). On the VPS this is
# /root/.hermes/google_token.json; all tools accept --token-path to override.
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_FILE=/path/to/google_token.json

# Drive folder IDs and run-output paths are data, not secrets — they live in
# scripts/research-wiki-tools/scan_config.py (scan pipeline) and as flags/defaults
# in pdf_backlog_triage.py. Optional overrides for the backlog indexer:
# RESEARCH_WIKI_INBOX_FOLDER_ID=your_drive_folder_id
# RESEARCH_WIKI_OUT_ROOT=/path/to/local/run/output
